1. Nf3 d5 2. g3 {I always prefer to start with this move.} ({After the popular
} 2. c4 {we need to reckon with} d4 {with a great amount of theory.}) 2... Bg4
({Let's suppose that Black plays} 2... Nf6 3. Bg2 Nc6 {Now, the threat is ...
e7-e5 and White should take measures. A careless move would be} 4. O-O ({
Also bad is} 4. b3 {when after} e5 5. Bb2 Bd6 {Black seizes a lot of space.}) (
{The correct move is} 4. d4) 4... e5 5. d3 Be7 6. Nbd2 O-O $15 {We have a Pirc
Reversed. Black is already fighting for an advantage.}) 3. Bg2 c6 4. O-O Nd7 5.
h3 Bh5 6. b3 e5 7. Bb2 Bd6 8. d3 Ngf6 9. Nbd2 O-O 10. c4 Re8 $15 {In the
arising structure, Black is slightly better in view of his stable space
advantage.} ({Even more precise would be} 10... e4 $17) *

