Of course, this move order is playable but it gives too many options to Black!
In my view, the REAL Reti move order is 1.Nf3-d5 2.g3! or 1.Nf3-Nf6 2.c4!} d4
3. e3 (3. b4 f6 (3... g5 $1 {this is a very very interesting move for black...
that objectively stands 100 per cent! ....ADD IT IN YOUR BLACK REPERTOIRE!})) (
3. d3 Nc6 $1 4. g3 e5 5. Bg2 Bb4+ 6. Bd2 a5 $15) (3. e4 Nc6 4. d3 e5 $17) 3...
Nc6 $1 {this line is one example where black gets a fine game with not much
effort!} (3... c5 4. exd4 cxd4 5. d3 Nc6 6. g3) 4. d3 (4. b4 dxe3 5. fxe3 Nxb4)
(4. exd4 Nxd4 5. Nxd4 Qxd4 6. Nc3 e5 $1 (6... Nh6) (6... c6 7. d3 Nh6) 7. d3
