1. c4 e6 2. g3 Nf6 3. Bg2 d5 4. Nf3 dxc4 5. Qa4+ Bd7 6. Qxc4 c5 7. Ne5 $5 {
this move has always been the main line..and white may try to be slightly
better......i prefer the Nc3-0-0-e4-Qe2 idea, though...} Qc8 8. Qd3 Nc6 9. Nxd7
Qxd7 10. Qxd7+ Kxd7 11. d3 (11. Nc3 Rc8 12. b3 (12. e3 b6 13. d3 Be7 14. Ke2
Rhd8 15. b3 Ke8 16. Bb2 Rd7 17. h3 h5 18. f4 g6 (18... Nd5) 19. Rhd1 Bf8 20.
Rac1 Bg7 21. Ba3) 12... Nd4 13. Rb1 b6 14. e3) 11... Be7 12. Nc3 Rac8 13. b3
