1. Nf3 d5 2. g3 Nc6 3. d4 {Of course 3...e5 should be prevented.} (3. Bg2 $6 e5
4. d3 {The reversed Pirc is not a good opening to utilise White's extra tempo.
Black has a full centre and no weaknesses.}) 3... Bg4 $5 (3... Bf5 {The other
serious move, leading to some kind of Jobava System with colours reversed.} 4.
Bg2 {Objectively the best continuation.} (4. a3 $5 {A somewhat "lazy" move.
White prevents any Nb4-ideas and argues that a2-a3 ia a useful move on its own.
} e6 ({If Black prepares long castling now with} 4... Qd7 5. b4 $5 $14 {
puts White's little pawn move to good use.}) 5. Bg2 Nf6 6. O-O Be7 7. c4 {
In the following lines, White can hope for a small advantage:} O-O (7... dxc4
8. Nbd2 $1 (8. Qa4 O-O 9. Qxc4 $14) 8... Na5 (8... O-O 9. Nxc4 $16) 9. Ne5 O-O
10. Ndxc4 Nxc4 11. Nxc4 Be4 12. Bxe4 Nxe4 13. Bf4 $14) 8. b3 Ne4 ({It might be
better to reroute the misplaced knight on c6 after} 8... h6 9. Bb2 Nb8 10. Nc3
