1. Nf3 d5 2. g3 c6 3. Bg2 Bf5 4. O-O Nd7 5. c4 e5 $6 {A very ambitious attempt
to seize the centre. White must act energetically now, to make use of his lead
in development.} 6. cxd5 cxd5 7. d4 $1 (7. d3 $5 {is another idea, preparing a
quick e2-e4.}) 7... e4 8. Ne5 {Threatening to put pressure on Black's centre
with Nc3 and Qb3. After} Nxe5 9. dxe5 {, Black has great difficulties
finishing his development while keeping his centre protected.} *

