1. Nf3 Nf6 2. c4 c6 3. g3 d5 4. Bg2 a6 $5 {Black played a waiting move, hoping
for White to commit in any way...} 5. O-O {... so White's best option is to
not commit.} dxc4 {should be the critical move now, preparing b7-b5 and trying
to justify a7-a6.} (5... g6 6. b3 Bg7 7. Bb2 O-O 8. d3 {is a theoretical line
in which a7-a6 doesn't look particularly useful.}) (5... Bf5 6. cxd5 cxd5 7.
Qb3 Qc8 8. Nc3 e6 9. d3 Nc6 10. Bf4 {resembles another line of the Reti where
the tempo lost on a7-a6 may turn out to be more of a weakening of Black's dark
squares than anything else.}) {White can now either play the sharp pawn
sacrifice} 6. Na3 ({or the safer} 6. a4 {, preparing Na3.}) 6... b5 7. d3 cxd3
8. Ne5 {, with a complicated position.} *

