1. Nf3 d5 2. g3 c5 3. Bg2 Nc6 4. d4 e6 {Probably the best move for Black. Due
to the fact that dynamic Grunfeld positions very much favour the player with
the extra tempo, he chooses a quiet setup.} 5. O-O Nf6 6. c4 {Now Black has
the choice between playing a Catalan ending or a Tarrasch Defence.} dxc4 (6...
cxd4 $6 {is good for White:} 7. Nxd4 Be7 (7... Nxd4 8. Qxd4 Be7 9. Nc3 dxc4 10.
Qxc4 O-O 11. Be3 $16) (7... Bc5 8. Nb3 Be7 9. cxd5 Nxd5 (9... exd5 10. Nc3 {
is an improved Tarrasch position for White.}) 10. Nc3 $3 Nxc3 11. Qxd8+ Nxd8
12. bxc3 O-O {, with a great Catalan-type ending for White after} 13. Rd1 $16 (
{or} 13. Rb1 $16)) 8. Nc3 {White delays c4xd5 as long as possible.} (8. cxd5
exd5 9. Nc3 O-O 10. Bf4 {would just lead to a regular Tarrasch position.}) 8...
O-O 9. Bf4 $1 {Now Black is running out of useful moves. For example:} Qb6 (
9... a6 10. Rc1) 10. Be3 $1 Ng4 11. cxd5 Nxe3 12. fxe3 $16) ({After} 6... Be7 {
, White can either transpose into a regular Tarrasch with} 7. cxd5 ({and} 7.
dxc5 Bxc5 8. a3 {If Black now prevents b2-b4 and Bb2 with} a5 {, the insertion
of those pawn moves should favour White, who can profit from the weakened
squares on Black's queenside after entering another Tarrasch-type position.} 9.
cxd5 exd5 $14) 7... exd5 8. b3 O-O 9. Bb2) 7. dxc5 {The following Catalan
ending is slightly better for White.} Qxd1 8. Rxd1 Bxc5 9. Nbd2 c3 (9... O-O $2
10. Nxc4 $16) 10. bxc3 O-O 11. Nb3 $1 (11. Ne1 $5 {is another way to play this
position:} Be7 12. Nd3 ({Or} 12. c4 $14) 12... Rd8 13. Bb2 $5 ({Or} 13. Nb3 $14
Nd5 14. Bd2)) 11... Be7 {White's main move now is} 12. c4 $14 ({Also
interesting is} 12. Nfd4 $5 Bd7 (12... Nxd4 $1 13. Rxd4 $5 (13. cxd4 Nd5 {
leads to a more stable position for Black.}) 13... e5 14. Rd1 Rb8 15. Na5 $14)
13. Nxc6 Bxc6 14. Bxc6 bxc6 15. c4 Rfd8 16. Bg5 Kf8 17. Bxf6 Bxf6 18. Rab1
Rxd1+ 19. Rxd1 Rd8 20. Rxd8+ ({Or} 20. Rb1) 20... Bxd8 21. Nd4 c5 22. Nb3 Bb6
23. f4 $14 {And in this minor piece ending, Black has to suffer quite a bit to
reach a draw.}) 12... Bd7 13. Bb2 Rfc8 (13... Rac8 14. c5 Rfd8 15. Nfd2 $14)
14. c5 $14 {White has lasting pressure.} *

