1. Nf3 d5 2. g3 c5 3. Bg2 Nc6 4. d4 Nf6 5. O-O cxd4 6. Nxd4 e5 7. Nxc6 bxc6 8.
c4 Be6 9. Bg5 Qd7 10. Bxf6 gxf6 11. e3 $3 $14 {A strong prophylactic move. Now
Black cannot really play d5-d4 anymore, which makes it even harder to deal
with the pressure against his centre.} h5 12. Nc3 Rd8 13. Qa4 $16 f5 14. Rfd1
e4 15. Bf1 $1 $18 {Miraculously, Anand went on to win from this losing
position.} Ke7 16. cxd5 cxd5 17. Nb5 $2 ({After} 17. Qa5 {, Black's position
falls apart.}) 17... Bg7 18. Rac1 Be5 19. Qb4+ Kf6 20. Nd4 Rc8 21. Ba6 Rxc1 22.
Rxc1 Rb8 23. Qd2 Qa4 24. Be2 Qxa2 25. Bxh5 Qxb2 26. Rc2 Qa1+ 27. Rc1 Rb1 28.
Rxb1 Qxb1+ 29. Kg2 Qd3 30. Qxd3 exd3 31. Nxe6 fxe6 32. f4 Bc3 33. Bd1 Ke7 34.
Kf3 Kd6 35. Ba4 Kc5 36. Bd7 Kd6 37. Ba4 a5 38. h3 e5 39. fxe5+ Bxe5 40. g4 Kc5
41. g5 Kb4 42. Bc6 Kc3 43. Ba4 Kb4 44. Bc6 a4 45. Bxd5 Kc3 0-1

