1. Nf3 c5 2. g3 Nc6 3. Bg2 d5 4. d4 e6 5. O-O f5 $2 {A positional blunder
without any merits. Black neglects his developments and weakens his position
on the light squares.} 6. c4 Nf6 ({After} 6... dxc4 {, White has the pleasant
choice between playing with queens on the board:} 7. Qa4 ({, and entering a
well-known favourable line from the Catalan with an extra tempo and an extra
weakening of Black's position:} 7. dxc5 Qxd1 8. Rxd1 Bxc5 9. Nbd2 c3 10. bxc3))
7. Nc3 Bd6 8. cxd5 $16 {In this Tarrasch-type position, Black would love to
spend another tempo or two to move his pawn back to f7.} exd5 9. dxc5 ({
Even better is} 9. Bg5 Be6 10. dxc5 Bxc5 11. Bxf6 Qxf6 12. Nxd5 $18) 9... Bxc5
10. Bg5 d4 11. Bxf6 Qxf6 12. Nd5 Qd8 13. Nd2 O-O 14. Rc1 Bb6 15. Nc4 Be6 16.
Nf4 Bf7 17. a3 Bc7 18. Nd3 Bd5 19. b4 Bxg2 20. Kxg2 Rc8 21. Nd2 f4 22. Qb3+ Kh8
23. Nf3 Qe7 24. Rc2 Bb6 25. Rfc1 Rce8 26. Nxf4 Rxf4 27. gxf4 Qe4 28. b5 Na5 29.
Qd3 Qxf4 30. Kh1 g6 31. Rc8 Rxc8 32. Rxc8+ Kg7 33. Re8 Qc1+ 34. Kg2 Qc4 35.
Re7+ Kf6 36. Qe4 Bc7 37. Qh4+ Kf5 38. Qg5# 1-0

